<br>
- (SI Only) The paperdoll image should no longer be corrupted by alt-tabbing in fullscreen mode. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(wonder if this fixes the rest of the textures getting farked...I got some screenshots that'd make acid trips look like a Nixon speech)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- You can no longer upgrade a keep door while mezzed, paralyzed, or in shade mode <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(apparently it's a sin to do anything in shade form...ya gotta wonder what bunch of drunk monkeys came up with the shade idea in first place...a *little* thought put into implementation before release (well, 'active beta') would have been nice...)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- If a necromancer is in a group which does all of the damage to a target without the necro/pet attacking at all and the rest of the group is killed, the monster should try to attack the pet, not the shade. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(Well at least they didn't try to blame is for &quot;exploiting&quot; on <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>that</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> one)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- Chat groups can hold up to 200 members <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(Good news but I can see cg leaders screaming in terror)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- Each time a player attempts to enter/exit stealth, a roughly one and a half second timer is set in which they can't attempt to do it again. This fixes the stealth spamming exploit. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(i.e. SpinyMice will die more often now trying to figure out if the combat timer is finished or not -- they just want his cheese!)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- Player guild messages and the guild Message Of The Day should now echo to other regions much more consistently. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(I've been bitching about that to them for a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>solid year</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->...but rank 0 <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>still</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> can't /release a keep...)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- A Necromancer's target window will now update to reflect a target his pet has acquired, if he does not already have a target. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(Still bugged but it's a start...I guess...hope it works better than the &quot;here&quot; command)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- Now, when you use any timer-based ability, spell, or combat style that has a timer, the spell/ability/style hotkey on your quickbar will now &quot;gray out&quot;. It will pop back into color mode once it's reusable again. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(That'll be nice...no more having to sit down to find out of MCL is up or not...hey, I wonder if the stealth icon will gray out?  Na, that'd be too logical <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- When a Necromancer's constitution drops to 3 or below, he can no longer summon a shade. This change should primarily affect Necromancers on the PvP servers. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(Don't faint, I agree with this one...you're not supposed to be able to fight with a con thatlow)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- If you are casting a non-targeted spell and your actual target dies or quits, it no longer cancels the spell. Examples of non targeted spells are: pet targeted, ground targeted or radius spells. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(Wonder if self-buffs are in that category -- annoys the crap out of me in PvE when I'm rebuffing mid-encounter (farking timed buffs) and get bit by that one)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- You should now get visual timers on your client when you Repair, Upgrade or Salvage. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(*there is a God!*)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- The following command states are now saved on the server: /SETWHO, /CANCELSTYLE and /NOQUEUE. The /COLORNAMES was always saved on the client by account and character. The /SPELLEFFECTS is not saved. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(About damned time they put /cancelstyle in the saved list...)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- The Theurgist realm ability Siege Bolt can now be used against targets that are in combat. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(...not gonna say it...but I should...)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- Necromancers in shade form can move through doors and stairs more easily. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(Ah...now if only the pet wouldn't try to run out the front door in some keeps while you go up the tower...well at least I don't have to jump put windows to exit the tower anymore.)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- Minstrels now receive Danger Sense, Distractions, Climb Walls, and Safe Fall I - V by specializing in their Stealth skill. They receive these abilities at the same spec levels that Infiltrators do. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(...well maybe it'll make Rasha happy, he can skeeter up a wall when Nami starts threatening him.)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Corpse Summoners are intended to help retrieve relics - some players are using corpse summoners to camp out in keeps and simply defend it, gaining Realm Points all the time. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(Well at least the zomebie-zerg will end *yahoo!*)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
NEW HATS <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(oh please...can't we have one hat a friar can wear with dignity? (/em wants a Circlet)  Welcome to Albion, Realm of the Dumbassed Hats.  Then again...who else things Hidien need a pointy hat? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
NEW CHAT GROUP COMMANDS <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(/cg leaders are still screaming in terror <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Now if we could just get the OTHER useful featuers of DToC in-game....)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
/cg listen - puts the chat group on listen mode. Only the moderator and leaders can speak. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>(I wonder, can you *really* make Albs listen??)</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
/cg leader - declare another member of the chat group as a leader. This player can invite other players into the chat group and speak when the chat group is on listen mode. <br>
/cg public - The chatgroup is public and anyone can join by typing /cg join <br>
/cg private - The chatgroup is invite or password only. <br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>(note that /cg Join is listed twice...</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
/cg join - joins a public chat group by name of the moderator. <br>
/cg join - joins a private chat group which has a password set. <br>
/cg password - display the current password for the chat group (moderator only) <br>
/cg password clear - clear the current password (moderator only) <br>
/cg password - set a new password <br>
<br>
<br>
ANIMATIONS <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(that -sounded- cool)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
- You now see an animation when drinking potions. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(haven't seen this one)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- You'll now see a graphical effect when you level. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(orthis one)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- Binding now has an animation. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(Oh my is it goofy too <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- A new effect has been added for when a Spellcraft overcharge goes horribly wrong. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(/em hopes for a mushroom cloud)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- You'll now see a special animation when /praying at your gravesite. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(/rude Mythic...I thought this would be an emote-type but it's just a spell effect...come ON, wtf is that worth?  (sorry, just saw some nice role-play in there tossed out for a goofy spell effect that makes little sense))</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- Three new emotes have been added - beg, induct, and dismiss. Use /beg to plead, /induct when inducting a new guild member (or other ceremonial occasion), and /dismiss to visually show someone that you're done with them. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(Beg is cool, dismiss is highly cool, induct is...well good for last rights or marriges but is about as grand as a hatbag, I'm sticking with /bow for induction ceremonies <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
NEW RVR &quot;CON&quot; COLORS  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(not at all happy about this myself...if they're &quot;a mystery&quot; to me, why can't I be a mystery to them?  Fair is fair)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Cleric Changes <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(Cool..I guess...healing proc is nice but gonna suck when it happens in reverse and lord knows rejuv clerics need SOMEthing to up their damage in melee)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
1) These spells are 10 minute group cast buffs, which for the duration give the chance to proc a healing effect when hit. <br>
2) These spells are 15 minute self buffs which raise melee damage output. <br>
<br>
Friar Changes <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(I gather these have not been modified and are, as has been proven, a <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">worse</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> spell to use over our group-heal which blows horridly)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Added group targeted heal-over-time spell to Rejuvenation spec track: <br>
<br>
Minstrel Changes <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(Good patch if you're a minstrel (or a recovering minstrel))</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
- Significantly increased values on the higher levels of the Song of Healing line. <br>
- Significantly reduced the cost of offensive shouts to be comparable to other classes. <br>
- Increased stun shout duration to be comparable to other single target stun spells. <br>
- Added new hit point buffer song (shoutable chant) <br>
<br>
Sorcerer Changes <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(that is SO gonna suck when other realms get it)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
- Increased Mind Spec AE Mez to 1875 range. <br>
<br>
Cabalist Changes <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(Not a bad day to be a cabby, pets have needed an overhaul for scalability for a long time -- shame they can still just be mostly ignored)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
- Changed Ruby Simulacrum proc to be a ranged spell that can be interrupted. <br>
- Increased melee damage on Sapphire Simulacrum. <br>
- Increased defense on Emerald Simulacrum and the damage on its DoT proc. <br>
- Increased damage on Jade Simulacrum's damage shield self buff. <br>
<br>
Now, attackers should be able to use Catapults to attack players and NPCs inside the keep, wear them down, then use a more limited number of Rams to get through the doors. Of course, keep defenders can also use Catapults and Ballistae to protect themselves. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(Overall I like the idea of bringing more than just 300rams to a relic-raid and it will make an albeit expensive replacement for earth-wizards...with /GTassist it could be even more interesting.)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- Ballista and Catapult ammo now stack up to 20. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(very interesting indeed)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- Only 3 siege weapons can now attack a door at the same time. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(Which means we might keep them power-relics a bit easier...taking 'em will be hard though.)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- The caster staff rewards for the level 40 guild quest have been changed. The new versions no longer have a proc; instead they now come with a charged effect. Anyone who completes the quests will now receive the new staffs. For anyone who has already completed the quests, an NPC has been added to each capital city that will gladly take the old staff and return the new one. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(Gee, thanks!  Now all I have to do is kill my pet, cast the charge, re-cast my pet, rebuff it....)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- The imp merchants of Darkness Falls will no longer aggro on characters from the realm they sell items for. They are also not attackable by the realm they sell items for. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(Damn...there goes my comic relief while in the merchant area)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Horse Routes...Albion <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(*sniff* *sniff* I'm gonna tear up here)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Castle Sauvage to West Cornwall <br>
West Cornwall to Castle Sauvage <br>
<br>
Caer Ulfwych to Snowdonia Fortress <br>
Snowdonia Fortress to Caer Ulfwych <br>
<br>
- A few new armor skins for the high teens to low 40's players have been added as new items in various places around the old lands and Shrouded Isles. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(heh, now younger friars can look more unique than those in friar epic armor?)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<br>
