<br>
Re: Minstrel. <br>
<br>
At level 30 the ablative shout is nice, it absorbs 25 hits, pulses like BT, somewhere around 5-6 sec/pulse? I looked at the line on the herald, and it dosen't look like it scales well. 25 at 30 inst is awesome, 45 at 40 inst is the sux.<br>
<br>
Shouts: I spammed those shouts any time they ungreyed and I had a hard time going oop. 2 shouts took less than 10% of my bar. I like this.<br>
<br>
In a chocolate world, they wouldn't take end at all. Previous to 1.60, I wouldn't start using shouts til I was OOE, or close. End cost is down, but in my mind not enough.<br>
<br>
Those silly little things minstrels got in stealth spec are going to keep them from getting actual help, later on. They're cute, but mostly fluff.<br>
<br>
But that said, I've been fooling around with a champ/bard combo. Bard=gimp with base buffs, thus far. I shoulda made a warden instead, and we all know how ubah wardens are.<br>
<br>
Oh, and BTW, your hotbars are all messed up, just like every other patch.<br>
<br>
Cleric changes.<br>
<br>
Fooled with this a tiny bit, haven't messed witht he self damage increase yet, not since early in the 1.60s, tried it on pend and it didn't do noticable ANYTHING.<br>
<br>
Played with the health proc a lot, grouped the mini-minstrel and cast, then disbanded and he went to town. Nice toy for the PL/enhance bot crowd. Tzill's delves at 90, and healed Skorii for anywhere between 44 and 98, and went off about as erraticly as you would expect.<br>
<br>
Shockingly enough, smite was slightly unnerfed. The spec DD should have gone to 3 sec when they nerfed the damage way back in the day, IMO.<br>
<br>
Re: Sorc mez. Nobody else SHOULD get that, it's sposed to be to offset the insta advantage. Sounds good to me.<br>
<br>
Cabalists: I'm told that you can't recycle your pet for more than it cost to cast anymore.<br>
<br>
Happy good news for alchies: you can FINALLY skill on the potions requiring dropped components. I didn't think they'd ever fix this, god forbid that the alchemists should have to pay less than 35g/attampt after 1001. or 70g/attempt after 1030. or 125/attempt after 1050. /sigh<br>
<br>
Coming soon to a keep take near you: Longshot and Volley have been made cheaper and the timers shortened to the point that it's ALMOST worth buying. If you could buy volley without buying longshot, it'd be a definate buy.<br>
<br>
What volley boils down to is you can shoot arrows at a ground target without LOS. It takes the normal amount of time, does the normal amount of damage, and misses the normal 80% of the time. Annoying , but not terribly dangerous.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.critshot.com" target="top">Critshot</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Find volley testing results at the above URL ( general forum)<br>
<br>
One lowlight I saw was that in 1 keep defence one archer burned through 600 arrows. That's about 24g of store bough arrows, and you can bet that isn't going to be happening every keep take. Plus, there never seems to be an arrow merchant in any of the keeps _I'm_ hanging out in. And you can only carry so many.<br>
<br>
The guy who shot off 600 arrows didn't gte a single kill, either. The only time this looks useful would be a zerg of people on the doors. You can't ground target it anywhere but at ground level ( unlike gtae) so it's useless for lord rooms.<br>
<br>
I will stop before my post becomes as long as Vince's. <br>
<br>
